│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs during loop-vectorization while VPlanTransforms tries to     │
│ simplify a VP recipe by folding live-in operands via InstSimplifyFolder.      │
│ Specifically, it attempts to fold an ExtractElement recipe where the vector   │
│ operand is actually a scalar constant (i32 0). InstructionSimplify's          │
│ simplifyExtractElementInst immediately casts the operand's type to            │
│ VectorType, asserting that the operand is a vector. Because the operand is    │
│ scalar, an assertion fires and opt aborts.                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ This matches the IR comment in the reproducer: "Make sure we don't try to     │
│ fold a Instruction::ExtractElement ir<0>, ir<0>, since we can't materialize   │
│ the live-in for the vector operand."                                          │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - The first transformation point identified is simplifyExtractElementInst in  │
│ InstructionSimplify.cpp.                                                      │
│ - The backtrace shows tryToFoldLiveIns calling                                │
│ InstSimplifyFolder::FoldExtractElement with ill-typed operands (Vec is i32    │
│ 0).                                                                           │
│ - Debugger locals show Ops[0] == 0x... (i32 0), Ops[1] is an index, and       │
│ Opcode == 62 (ExtractElement). The immediate assert in                        │
│ simplifyExtractElementInst casts Vec->getType() to VectorType.                │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ VPlanTransforms::tryToFoldLiveIns assumes that if all operands are live-ins,  │
│ it can hand them to InstSimplifyFolder. However, for certain VP recipes (like │
│ ExtractElement), the VP graph may have scalar live-ins in places where the    │
│ instruction semantics require a vector (e.g., an extractelement of a vector). │
│ Passing such ill-typed operands to InstSimplifyFolder leads to                │
│ InstructionSimplify assuming well-typed IR and asserting.                     │
│                                                                               │
│ Therefore, the bug is that tryToFoldLiveIns does not verify operand types for │
│ instructions with strict type requirements (ExtractElement, InsertElement,    │
│ etc.) before attempting to fold.                                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanTransforms.cpp                     │
│ - Location: tryToFoldLiveIns switch handling of InsertElement and             │
│ ExtractElement (lines 983–987 in provided snapshot).                          │
│ - Change: Add type guards to ensure the vector operand is actually            │
│ vector-typed before calling InstSimplifyFolder. If not, bail out and return   │
│ nullptr so no folding is attempted.                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Proposed patch (conceptual):                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ Replace existing cases:                                                       │
│   case Instruction::InsertElement:                                            │
│     return Folder.FoldInsertElement(Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2]);                  │
│   case Instruction::ExtractElement:                                           │
│     return Folder.FoldExtractElement(Ops[0], Ops[1]);                         │
│                                                                               │
│ With guarded versions:                                                        │
│   case Instruction::InsertElement: {                                          │
│     if (!isa<VectorType>(Ops[0]->getType()))                                  │
│       return nullptr;                                                         │
│     return Folder.FoldInsertElement(Ops[0], Ops[1], Ops[2]);                  │
│   }                                                                           │
│   case Instruction::ExtractElement: {                                         │
│     if (!isa<VectorType>(Ops[0]->getType()))                                  │
│       return nullptr;                                                         │
│     return Folder.FoldExtractElement(Ops[0], Ops[1]);                         │
│   }                                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Rationale:                                                                    │
│ - Prevents calling simplifyExtractElementInst/simplifyInsertElementInst with  │
│ ill-typed operands, preserving the precondition that the IR being folded is   │
│ well-typed.                                                                   │
│ - Matches the intent spelled out in the reproducer comment: do not try to     │
│ fold extractelement ir<0>, ir<0> when you can't materialize the vector        │
│ live-in.                                                                      │
│ - Keeps the change localized to VPlanTransforms, which is the origin of the   │
│ incorrect folding request, rather than weakening assertions in the more       │
│ general InstSimplify code.                                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is caused by VPlanTransforms::tryToFoldLiveIns attempting to fold   │
│ an ExtractElement with scalar live-ins, violating type invariants expected by │
│ InstSimplify and triggering an assertion. Adding vector type checks before    │
│ calling the Folder for ExtractElement (and symmetrically for InsertElement)   │
│ avoids ill-typed folding, preventing the assertion and aligning behavior with │
│ the reproducer's expectation. This fix prevents the abort while preserving    │
│ all valid simplifications.                                                    │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
│                                                                               │
